and when they were come into the town they found revellers bound from house to house and leaning from windows and balconies , who listened to the songs of iranon and tossed him flowers and applauded when he was done .
then for a moment did iranon believe he had found those who thought and felt even as he , though the town was not a hundredth as fair as aira .
when dawn came iranon looked about with dismay , for the domes of oonai were not golden in the sun , but grey and dismal .
