and the king bade him put away his tattered purple , and clothed him in satin and , with rings of green jade and bracelets of tinted ivory , and lodged him in a gilded and tapestried chamber on a bed of sweet carven wood with canopies and coverlets of flower embroidered silk .
thus dwelt iranon in oonai , the city of lutes and dancing .
