after the beam came clouds , and then i slept .
and it was under a horned waning moon that i saw the city for the first time .
still and somnolent did it lie , on a strange plateau in a hollow between strange peaks .
of ghastly marble were its walls and its towers , its columns , domes , and pavements .
in the marble streets were marble pillars , the upper parts of which were carven into the images of grave bearded men .
the air was warm and stirred not .
