alone i mounted the tower , for every man of stout body was needed in the passes below .
my brain was sore dazed with excitement and fatigue , for i had not slept in many days ; yet was my purpose firm , for i loved my native land of lomar , and the marble city olathoe that lies betwixt the peaks noton and kadiphonek .
